{"title_page": "Eddie Gutierrez (actor)", "text_new": "{{short description|Filipino actor}}\n{{BLP sources|date=June 2010}}\n{{Philippine name|Pickett|Gutierrez}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name        = Eddie Guti\u00e9rrez\n|image=\n|caption     =\n|birth_name  = Eduardo Pickett Guti\u00e9rrez Sr.\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1942|02|6}}\n|birth_place = [[Ermita, Manila]], [[Commonwealth of the Philippines]]\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|other_names = Eddie, J.E.G.\n|known_for   =\n|occupation  = Actor\n|nationality = [[Philippine nationality law|Filipino]]\n|spouse      = {{marriage|[[Annabelle Rama]]|November 8, 1980}}\n|children    = 8, including [[Tonton Gutierrez|Tonton]], [[Ruffa Gutierrez|Ruffa]], [[Richard Gutierrez|Richard]] and [[Raymond Gutierrez|Raymond]]\n|partner = [[Liza Lorena]] (1963-1964; separated)<br>[[Pilita Corrales]] (1968-1971; separated)\n|parents     = Antonio Atayde Gutierrez Jr.<br>Mary Rufina Herranz Pickett\n|years_active = 1959\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Eduardo Pickett Guti\u00e9rrez''' (born February 6, 1942), professionally known as '''Eddie Guti\u00e9rrez''', is a [[Filipino people|Filipino]] actor and former matinee idol.\n\n==Early life==\nGuti\u00e9rrez was born at 4:50 AM on February 6, 1942 at Manila Doctors Hospital in [[Ermita, Manila]].<ref name=\"birth\">{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-1-14204-8716-77?cc=1686086&wc=M8LY-JMS:129556201,132427501,148074401|title=Eddie Gutierrez's Birth Certificate|publisher=|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref> He is the son of Antonio Atayde Guti\u00e9rrez, Jr. (August 5, 1913 in [[Santa Mesa, Manila]] \u2013 February 10, 1954 in [[Santa Mesa, Manila]])<ref name=\"father death\">{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-267-12374-26160-20?cc=1686086&wc=M8LT-V6F:129556401,129867501,144821701|title=Antonio Gutierrez's Death Certificate|publisher=|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref> and Mary Rufina Herranz Pickett (born November 24, 1916 in [[Tondo, Manila]]).<ref name=\"mary pickett\">{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-1-15575-8211-17?cc=1686086&wc=M8LL-3Z9:129556201,129598201,133127701|title=Mary Pickett's Birth Certificate|publisher=|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref> His parents were married on April 14, 1939 in [[Santa Mesa, Manila]].<ref name=\"parents' marriage\">{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-1-12228-80774-83?cc=1686086&wc=M8LK-6NG:129556101,129799101,132033802|title=Antonio Gutierrez, Jr. and Mary Pickett's Marriage Certificate|publisher=|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nHis paternal grandfather was Antonio Mar\u00eda Rogelio Guti\u00e9rrez del Campo (September 16, 1866 in [[Santander, Spain]] \u2013 June 21, 1952 in [[Santa Mesa, Manila]]),<ref name=\"antonio baptism\">{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-266-11678-83601-62?cc=2078544&wc=SDPM-2NG:357504401,361271701,361271702,361349801|title=Antonio Mar\u00eda Rogelio Guti\u00e9rrez's Bapstimal Register|publisher=|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"antonio death\">{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-1-14160-1118-15?cc=1686086&wc=M8LL-BM9:129556201,129646401,133887701|title=Antonio Guti\u00e9rrez del Campo's Death Certificate|publisher=|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref> while his maternal grandfather was John Thomas Pickett (February 17, 1868 in [[Ontario, Canada]] - March 8, 1939 in [[Manila]]).\n\n==Education==\nHe studied at [[San Beda College]] and finished high school at [[San Sebastian College]]. He took up a course in Commerce at [[Letran College]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHe married [[Anabelle Rama]] on November 8, 1980,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2017/02/13/1671606/eddie-proposes-annabelle|title=Eddie proposes to Annabelle|first=Ricky|last=Lo|publisher=|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref> with whom he has six children; [[Ruffa Gutierrez|Ruffa]], Rocky, Elvis, [[Richard Gutierrez|Richard]], [[Raymond Gutierrez|Raymond]] and Ritchie Paul. His wife serves as the talent manager for his children who are in the entertainment industry.\nHe also had two children from previous relationships; [[Tonton Gutierrez|Tonton]] with actress [[Liza Lorena]] in 1964 and Ramon Christoper Gutierrez with singer [[Pilita Corrales]] in 1969 and also known to be the grandfather of actress-singer [[Janine Gutierrez]], the daughter of Ramon Christopher Gutierrez.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dumaual|first1=Miguel|title=Pilita on Eddie Gutierrez: I loved him|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/07/03/12/pilita-eddie-gutierrez-i-loved-him|website=ABS-CBN News|accessdate=19 September 2014|date=7 March 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nA bit player in ''Prinsesang Gusgusin'' (1958), Gutierrez was introduced in ''Handsome'' (1959) and played the lead in films like ''Kaming makasalanan'' (1960), ''Eddie Longlegs'' (1964), ''Portrait of My Love'' (1965) and ''Pogi'' (1967). He was under contract for Sampaguita Pictures for eight years. His other films include ''Hiram na Kamay'' (1962), ''June Bride'' (1962), ''Pitong puso'' (1962), ''Sabina'' (1963), ''Bird of Paradise'' (1963), ''Eddie Loves Susie'' (1964), ''Isinulat sa Dugo'' (1965), ''I'll Dream of You'' (1966), and ''All Over the World'' (1967).\n\nAfter living in the United States for several years, he came back to the Philippines with his family and resumed his acting career. He appeared in ''Katawang lupa'' (1975), ''Ursula'' (1976), ''Beerhouse'' (1977), ''Bontoc'' (1977), ''Balatkayo'' (1978), ''Bomba Star'' (1980), ''Sari-saring ibong kulasisi'' (1978), ''Lagi na lamang ba akong babae?'' (1978), and ''Lumakad Ka, Gabi'' (1979).\n\nIn 1991, he was nominated Best Supporting Actor by the Film Academy of the Philippines (FAP) for ''Uubusin ko ang lahi mo'' (1991).{{Citation needed|date=August 2010}} He received the FAP award for Best Actor and the Filipino Academy of Movie Arts & Sciences (FAMAS) for Best Supporting Actor for ''Ikaw pa lang ang minahal'' (1992).{{Citation needed|date=August 2010}}\n\nIn 2004 and 2006, Guti\u00e9rrez joined the cast of the TV fantasy series, ''[[Mulawin]]'' and ''[[Majika]]'' in both series playing an elder with magical powers.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Films===\n{|class=\"wikitable table\"\n! Title \n! Role \n! Year \n|- \n| Batas ng Alipin \n| \n| 1955 \n|-\n| Handsome \n| \n| 1959 \n|- \n| Ipinagbili Kami ng Aming Tatay \n| \n| 1959 \n|- \n| Pitong Pagsisisi \n| \n| 1959 \n|- \n| Wedding Bells \n| Mike (segment \"Pagmamanhikan\") \n| 1959 \n|-\n| Dobol Trobol \n| \n| 1960 \n|- \n| Kwintas ng Alaala \n| \n| 1960 \n|- \n| Beatnik \n| \n| 1960 \n|- \n| Estela Mondragon \n| \n| 1960 \n|- \n| Ginang Hukom\n| Kyle (segment \"Ama at anak\") \n| 1960 \n|- \n| Dalawang Kalbaryo ni Dr. Mendez \n| \n| 1961 \n|- \n| Joey, Eddie, Lito\n| Eddie \n| 1961 \n|- \n| Octavia \n| \n| 1961 \n|- \n| Pitong Puso \n| \n| 1962 \n|- \n| Susanang Daldal \n| \n| 1962 \n|- \n| The Big Broadcast \n| Eddie \n| 1962 \n|- \n| Tanzan The Mighty \n| \n| 1962 \n|- \n| June Bride \n| \n| 1962 \n|- \n| Siyam na Langit\n| \n| 1962 \n|- \n| Bird of Paradise \n| \n| 1963 \n|- \n| Sabina \n| Eddie \n| 1963 \n|- \n| Apat Ang Anak ni David \n| \n| 1963 \n|- \n| Eddie Loves Susie \n| \n| 1963 \n|- \n| Amaliang Mali-Mali Vs. Susanang Daldal\n| Daldal's companion \n| 1963 \n|- \n| Fighting Warays sa Ilokos \n| \n| 1964 \n|- \n| Walang Takot sa Patalim \n| \n| 1964 \n|- \n| Jukebox Jamboree \n| \n| 1964 \n|- \n| Leron Leron Sinta \n| \n| 1964 \n|- \n| Magkapatid na Waray \n| \n| 1964 \n|- \n| Mga Kanyon sa Corregidor \n| \n| 1964 \n|- \n| Hi-Sosayti \n| \n| 1964\n|- \n| Portrait of My Love \n| \n| 1965 \n|- \n| Bye Bye na Daddy \n| \n| 1965 \n|- \n| Hamon sa Kampeon \n| \n| 1965 \n|- \n| Ang Maganda Kong Kapitbahay \n| \n| 1965 \n|- \n| Isinulat na Dugo \n| \n| 1965 \n|- \n| Alis D'yan Huwag Mo Akong Ligawan \n| \n| 1966 \n|- \n| Walastik na Downtown \n| \n| 1966  \n|- \n| Sexy Yata yan\n|\n| 1966\n|-\n| Ang Pangarap Ko'y Ikaw\n| Chito/Rene\n| 1967\n|-\n| Pogi